# Megabyte Mentors Backend - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to configure your Render.com deployment

# ============================================
# REQUIRED ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ============================================

# MongoDB Connection String
# Get this from MongoDB Atlas: Database → Connect → Drivers
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/megabyte-mentors?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# JWT Secret Token (Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
# IMPORTANT: Use a strong, random value in production
TOKEN_SECRET=your-secret-token-here-change-this-to-random-string

# Server Port (Render will use this)
PORT=3000

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ============================================

# Email Service Configuration (if using email features)
# EMAIL_SERVICE=gmail
# EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password

# Expo Push Notifications (if implemented)
# EXPO_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-expo-access-token

# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================

# 1. NEVER commit this file with real values to git
# 2. Add real values in Render.com Dashboard → Environment Variables
# 3. Generate TOKEN_SECRET with: openssl rand -base64 32
# 4. MongoDB Atlas: Allow access from 0.0.0.0/0 (or Render IPs)
# 5. Keep this file as reference only

# ============================================
# HOW TO GENERATE TOKEN_SECRET
# ============================================

# On Mac/Linux:
# openssl rand -base64 32

# On Windows (PowerShell):
# [Convert]::ToBase64String((1..32 | ForEach-Object { Get-Random -Maximum 256 }))

# Or use online generator:
# https://generate-random.org/api-key-generator
